Outlier Removal

# sold_price
x <- data$sold_price

Q1 <- quantile(x, probs=.25)
Q3 <- quantile(x, probs=.75)
iqr = Q3-Q1
upper_limit = Q3 + (iqr*1.5)
lower_limit = Q1 - (iqr*1.5)
data_no_outliers <- subset(data, (x <= upper_limit) & (x >= lower_limit))

# photo_count
x <- data_no_outliers$photo_count

Q1 <- quantile(x, probs=.25)
Q3 <- quantile(x, probs=.75)
iqr = Q3-Q1
upper_limit = Q3 + (iqr*1.5)
lower_limit = Q1 - (iqr*1.5)
data_no_outliers <- subset(data_no_outliers, (x <= upper_limit) & (x >= lower_limit))

# living_area
x <- data_no_outliers$living_area

Q1 <- quantile(x, probs=.25)
Error in quantile.default(x, probs = 0.25) : 
  missing values and NaN's not allowed if 'na.rm' is FALSE

ggplot2 Visualizations

Price Analysis

data_no_outliers$property_type <- as.factor(data_no_outliers$property_type)


p <- ggplot(data_no_outliers, aes(y = sold_price, x = property_type, fill = property_type )) 
 
p +  geom_boxplot() +
     theme_bw() 

    
# Re-order items
p + geom_boxplot() +
    theme_bw() +
    scale_x_discrete(limits=c("CND", "DUP", "TNH", "SGL", "PAT", "OTH")) 



ggplot(data_no_outliers, aes(y = sold_price, living_area )) + 
geom_smooth(aes(colour = factor(corona_crisis)))


ggplot(data = data_no_outliers) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(x = living_area, y = sold_price, color = corona_crisis))


ggplot(data = data_no_outliers) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(y = sold_price, living_area )) + 
  facet_wrap(corona_crisis ~ property_type, nrow = 2)


ggplot(data = data_no_outliers) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = property_type, fill = condition))


ggplot(data = data_no_outliers) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = condition)) 


# Ordered and "Other" is removed
ggplot(data = data_no_outliers) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = condition)) +
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("avg", "Excellent", "fair", "New", "Poor", "Vrgd"))
